{
  "stem": "8.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And, on that Sunday-- March 19 was a Sunday-- he traveled to Budapest and he was arrested at the railroad station and did not return home, and we didn't know what happened to him.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "My mother just returned that Sunday morning from visiting her parents in Edeleny.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I, I felt terrified that day what was going to happen to us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "When the-- when the Germans marched into Hungary, everything that happened in other countries that took months or a year or years, it happened here very quickly.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So that only the following week, we were given the order to wear the yellow star and to give up all our businesses.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, following that to go into the ghetto, which was in the same place, in the same Miskolc.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And, since I lived in that area, which was designated as the ghetto, people came to stay with us rather than us having to go somewhere else.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now, of course, because our business was closed and because we no longer can employ non-Jews, the maids left.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, they were too scared to come and, and visit us or to help us out.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We lived in a, in an apartment house where there were some non-Jews, and I don't know exactly what happened to them, whether they had to move out or not.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't remember that clearly.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was a, a super, who was like a janitor, in the building and I think he-- they moved out, eventually, and somebody else moved into their apartment, but I'm not sure about that.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The 19th was the beginning of, of the reality that we could not face.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
